# docs/assets Directory Structure

This directory contains all visual assets for the BizScout project documentation and branding.

## Directory Organization

```
docs/
└── assets/
    ├── logo/              # Logo files in various formats
    │   ├── svg/           # Vector logo files
    │   ├── png/           # Raster logo files
    │   └── favicon/       # Browser and app icons
    ├── screenshots/       # Application screenshots
    │   ├── dashboard/     # Dashboard views
    │   ├── businesses/    # Business listing views
    │   ├── maps/          # Map visualization views 
    │   └── jobs/          # Scraping jobs views
    ├── diagrams/          # Architecture and flow diagrams
    │   ├── architecture/  # System architecture diagrams
    │   ├── database/      # Database schema diagrams
    │   └── flow/          # User flow and process diagrams
    ├── social/            # Social media assets
    └── mockups/           # Design mockups and wireframes
```

## Asset List

### Logo Files

- **logo/svg/bizscout-logo.svg**: Full color vector logo
- **logo/svg/bizscout-logo-white.svg**: White (reversed) vector logo
- **logo/svg/bizscout-mark.svg**: Logo mark only (no text)
- **logo/png/bizscout-logo-full.png**: Full logo with text (1200×300)
- **logo/png/bizscout-logo-square.png**: Square logo (500×500)
- **logo/png/bizscout-mark.png**: Icon only (256×256)

### Favicon Files

- **logo/favicon/favicon.ico**: Multi-size favicon (16×16, 32×32, 48×48)
- **logo/favicon/favicon-16x16.png**: Small favicon (16×16)
- **logo/favicon/favicon-32x32.png**: Medium favicon (32×32)
- **logo/favicon/apple-touch-icon.png**: iOS home screen icon (180×180)
- **logo/favicon/android-chrome-192x192.png**: Android icon (192×192)
- **logo/favicon/android-chrome-512x512.png**: Large Android icon (512×512)
- **logo/favicon/site.webmanifest**: Web app manifest file
- **logo/favicon/safari-pinned-tab.svg**: Safari pinned tab icon

### Screenshots

- **screenshots/dashboard/dashboard-overview.png**: Main dashboard view
- **screenshots/dashboard/dashboard-analytics.png**: Analytics dashboard view
- **screenshots/businesses/business-list.png**: Business listing page
- **screenshots/businesses/business-detail.png**: Business detail page
- **screenshots/maps/map-view.png**: Interactive map view
- **screenshots/maps/heatmap-view.png**: Business density heatmap
- **screenshots/jobs/scraping-job-list.png**: Job list view
- **screenshots/jobs/scraping-job-detail.png**: Job details and progress view
- **screenshots/jobs/new-job-form.png**: New job creation form

### Diagrams

- **diagrams/architecture/system-overview.png**: High-level system architecture
- **diagrams/architecture/component-diagram.png**: Component interactions
- **diagrams/database/db-schema.png**: Database schema diagram
- **diagrams/flow/user-flow.png**: User journey diagram
- **diagrams/flow/data-flow.png**: Data processing flow
- **diagrams/flow/scraping-process.png**: Scraping job workflow

### Social Media Assets

- **social/github-banner.png**: GitHub repository banner (1280×640)
- **social/og-image.png**: Open Graph preview image (1200×630)
- **social/twitter-card.png**: Twitter card image (1200×600)
- **social/linkedin-banner.png**: LinkedIn profile banner (1584×396)

### Mockups and Wireframes

- **mockups/landing-page.png**: Landing page design
- **mockups/dashboard.png**: Dashboard wireframe
- **mockups/mobile-views.png**: Mobile responsive designs

## Usage Guidelines

1. **Logo Usage**:
   - Use SVG formats whenever possible for crisp rendering
   - Maintain proper spacing around logo (padding equal to 25% of logo height)
   - Don't alter colors or proportions of the logo

2. **Screenshots**:
   - Keep screenshot aspect ratios consistent (16:9 recommended)
   - Use 1280×720 or 1920×1080 resolution when possible
   - Avoid showing sensitive information or test data

3. **Diagrams**:
   - Use consistent styling across all diagrams
   - Export in PNG format with transparent background
   - Include a legend when necessary

4. **Directory Maintenance**:
   - Keep filenames descriptive but concise
   - Use hyphen-case for all filenames (e.g., `business-detail.png`)
   - Update screenshots whenever significant UI changes occur
